A former school teacher and Bengals cheerleader charged with having sex with one of her 16-year-old students has accepted a plea deal.

Sarah Jones, 27, is due in court on Monday to accept the deal and be sentenced, according to sources.

Her mother Cheryl Jones, a school principal, is also expected to accept a plea deal tomorrow after she was charged over tampering with evidence in her daughter's case.

